# Environment variables — example template.
# Copy this to `.env.local` (which is gitignored) and fill in values as needed.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_API_BASE_URL
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The base URL of the TTB verification backend.
#
# Leave EMPTY (or omit the variable) to run in MOCK mode — the bundled
# fixtures in src/api/mockData.ts are served instead of hitting any network.
# This is the default for local development and for the initial deploy.
#
# When the real backend is live, set this to its URL (no trailing slash):
#
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.ttb-label-verification.example.gov
#
# The client (src/api/client.ts) auto-detects: if VITE_API_BASE_URL is set,
# USE_MOCK flips to false and the same verifyLabel / verifyBatch functions
# POST to ${VITE_API_BASE_URL}/verify and /verify-batch instead.
#
VITE_API_BASE_URL=
